FBIS4-37105 "drnes117_k_94007" FBIS-NES-94-117 Daily Report 8 Jun 1994 IRAQ Religious Awareness Committees Cable Support Religious Awareness Committees Cable Support JN1706063494 Baghdad AL-THAWRAH in Arabic 8 Jun 94 p 6 JN1706063494 Baghdad AL-THAWRAH Arabic BFN [Text] The leader president has received cables from the Religious Awareness Committees [Lijan al-Taw'iyah al-Diniyah] in al-Ta'mim, al-Anbar, and Babil Governorates in which they evaluated his excellency's decision to cancel horse racing and gambling and to build the Grand State Mosque instead. The committees affirmed that this blessed step reinforces the progress of the faith campaign [al-hamlah al-imaniyah] which is lived by our steadfast, struggler people under the flag of Allahu Akbar, which is carried by the symbol and pride of Iraq, struggler leader President Saddam Husayn. The members of the Religious Awareness Committees prayed to Almight God to preserve struggler leader President Saddam Husayn as an asset for Iraq and the Arab nation.
